				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Training points<a name="32415"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 1 04 10:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yeah, the exception is Rogues.  Though they can use bows, they can critical hit with throwing weapons and get access to the Mrylokar's stuff that summons daggers so throwing is worth while to them to some extent, but the range of the bow or spell is usually why its used, and bard song is the same way, most cheap throwing weapons are either heavy/unstackable or have lousy range which makes them useless compared to a song combined with a range item.  And in my opinion, I'd say just because you can't disarm a trap doesn't mean that sense is useless.  In LDoN there are three different kinds that take three different people to disarm them.  If you can sense the trap, then you know that only a bard or rogue can disarm it and there's no point in bothering if you don't have anyone with the right skill.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
